         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Oct. 6 /80 ¶ My dear Von Mueller ¶  ¶ The Livistona has arrived &amp; seemingly in very good order. ¶  We are having it potted &amp; shall do our best to bring it round &amp; shall let you know the result. ¶  ¶ V...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.10.06</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew.</p>
               </note>Oct. 6 /80</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The <name key="Livistona">Livistona</name> has arrived &amp; seemingly in very good order.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 20 July 1880.</p>
               </note> We are having it potted &amp; shall do our best to bring it round &amp; shall let you know the result.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Very likely the Palms are, like the tree ferns, divisible into those that will, &amp; those that will not stand that sort of "heroic" treatment.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are constantly shifting our Palms in the Palm House from pots to tubs &amp; from these to bigger tubs, &amp; we find that some are killed by the process, others not.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am extremely obliged for the Palm specimens, which are great prizes.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos. D. Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">The big tree fern trunk (D. antarctica) which you sent some 6 years ago is a splendid sight, &amp; the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Todea">Todea</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> goes on magnificently.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Dicksonia%20antarctica">Dicksonia antarctica</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Livistona">Livistona</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Todea">Todea</name>
            </p>
         </div>
